<h2>reverseR: Linear Regression Stability to Significance Reversal</h2>
<p>Tests linear regressions for significance reversal through leave-one(multiple)-out and shifting/addition of response values. The paradigm of the package is loosely based on the somewhat forgotten "dfstat" criterion (Belsley, Kuh &amp; Welsch 1980 &lt;<a href="https://doi.org/10.1002%2F0471725153.ch2">doi:10.1002/0471725153.ch2</a>&gt;), which tests influential values in linear models from their effect on statistical inference, i.e. changes in p-value.</p>
